  <h1>About Clay Garden Press</h1>

  <p>Clay Garden Press is a small independent publication. Field notes from people who actually do the thing, written for people who want to learn from working examples instead of marketing.</p>

  <p>We cover narrow topics deeply rather than broad topics shallowly. If we're writing about something, it's because we either spent real time on it or know someone who did. We cite our sources. We update posts when we learn we got something wrong.</p>

  <h2>What you can expect</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>Long-form posts (1,500–2,500 words typical) over short hot takes</li>
    <li>Specific examples, real numbers, named tools — not generic advice</li>
    <li>Affiliate links only on things we'd actually use (see <a href="/privacy/">privacy &amp; disclosures</a>)</li>
    <li>No pop-ups, no autoplay video, no aggressive newsletter modal</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Reach us at <a href="mailto:hello@claygardenpress.com">hello@claygardenpress.com</a>.</p>
